RAPULA MOATSHE Security guards have embarked on a march outside Tshwane House after the City of Tshwane refused to renew contracts of private security companies under which they worked.They chanted slogans denouncing the DA-led administration under mayor Solly Msimanga.The guards refused to depart from the city's new headquarters until they were addressed by Msimanga.Their leader Isaac Sibanda said workers marched to the municipal offices after the city manager Moeketsi Mosola refused to renew contracts of private security companies.